  urldate = {2025-02-17},
  abstract = {We show that the core of a weakly group-theoretical braided fusion category \$\textbackslash C\$ is equivalent as a braided fusion category to a tensor product \$\textbackslash B \textbackslash boxtimes \textbackslash D\$, where \$\textbackslash D\$ is a pointed weakly anisotropic braided fusion category, and \$\textbackslash B \textbackslash cong \textbackslash vect\$ or \$\textbackslash B\$ is an Ising braided category. In particular, if \$\textbackslash C\$ is integral, then its core is a pointed weakly anisotropic braided fusion category. As an application we give a characterization of the solvability of a weakly group-theoretical braided fusion category. We also prove that an integral modular category all of whose simple objects have Frobenius-Perron dimension at most 2 is necessarily group-theoretical.},
